140  P.PreControlClusterIdCaseThreshold = 0;
141  P.R0scale = 1.0;

155  {
156  GotO = 1;

166  {

168  }
169  else if (argv[i][1] == 'L' && argv[i][2] == ':')
170  {
171  GotL = 1;
172  P.LoadSaveNetwork = 1;
173  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%s", NetworkFile);
174  }
175  else if (argv[i][1] == 'S' && argv[i][2] == ':')
176  {
177  P.LoadSaveNetwork = 2;
178  GotS = 1;
179  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%s", NetworkFile);
180  }
181  else if (argv[i][1] == 'R' && argv[i][2] == ':')
182  {
183  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%lf", &P.R0scale);
184  }
185  else if (argv[i][1] == 'K' && argv[i][2] == 'P' && argv[i][3] == ':') //added Kernel Power and Offset scaling so that it can easily be altered from the command line in order to vary the kernel quickly: ggilani - 15/10/14
186  {
187  sscanf(&argv[i][4], "%lf", &P.KernelPowerScale);
188  }
189  else if (argv[i][1] == 'K' && argv[i][2] == 'O' && argv[i][3] == ':')
190  {
191  sscanf(&argv[i][4], "%lf", &P.KernelOffsetScale);
192  }
193  else if (argv[i][1] == 'C' && argv[i][2] == 'L' && argv[i][3] == 'P' && argv[i][4] == '1' && argv[i][5] == ':') // generic command line specified param - matched to #1 in param file
194  {
195  sscanf(&argv[i][6], "%lf", &P.clP1);
196  }
197  else if (argv[i][1] == 'C' && argv[i][2] == 'L' && argv[i][3] == 'P' && argv[i][4] == '2' && argv[i][5] == ':') // generic command line specified param - matched to #2 in param file

202  {

206  {
207  sscanf(&argv[i][6], "%lf", &P.clP4);
208  }
209  else if(argv[i][1] == 'C' && argv[i][2] == 'L' && argv[i][3] == 'P' && argv[i][4] == '5' && argv[i][5] == ':') // generic command line specified param - matched to #5 in param file
210  {
211  sscanf(&argv[i][6], "%lf", &P.clP5);
212  }
213  else if(argv[i][1] == 'C' && argv[i][2] == 'L' && argv[i][3] == 'P' && argv[i][4] == '6' && argv[i][5] == ':') // generic command line specified param - matched to #6 in param file
214  {
215  sscanf(&argv[i][6], "%lf", &P.clP6);
216  }

219  GotAP = 1;

223  {
224  GotScF = 1;
225  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%s", SchoolFile);
226  }
227  else if (argv[i][1] == 'T' && argv[i][2] == ':')

238  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%s", RegDemogFile);
239  }

241  {
242  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%i", &P.MaxNumThreads);
243  }
244  else if (argv[i][1] == 'M' && argv[i][2] == ':')
245  {
246  P.OutputDensFile = 1;
247  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%s", OutDensFile);
248  }
249  else if (argv[i][1] == 'I' && argv[i][2] == ':')
250  {
251  sscanf(&argv[i][3], "%s", InterventionFile[P.DoInterventionFile]);
252  P.DoInterventionFile++;
253  }
254  else if (argv[i][1] == 'L' && argv[i][2] == 'S' && argv[i][3] == ':')
255  {
256  sscanf(&argv[i][4], "%s", SnapshotLoadFile);
257  P.DoLoadSnapshot = 1;
258  }
259  else if (argv[i][1] == 'P' && argv[i][2] == 'P' && argv[i][3] == ':')
260  {
261  sscanf(&argv[i][4], "%s", PreParamFile);
262  GotPP = 1;
263  }
264  else if (argv[i][1] == 'S' && argv[i][2] == 'S' && argv[i][3] == ':')
265  {
266  sscanf(&argv[i][4], "%s", buf);
267  fprintf(stderr, "### %s\n", buf);
268  sep = strchr(buf, ',');
269  if (!sep)
270  Perr = 1;
271  else
272  {
273  P.DoSaveSnapshot = 1;
274  *sep = ' ';
275  sscanf(buf, "%lf %s", &(P.SnapshotSaveTime), SnapshotSaveFile);
276  }
277  }
278  }
279  if (((GotS) && (GotL)) || (!GotP) || (!GotO)) Perr = 1;
280  }

283 
284  sprintf(OutFile, "%s", OutFileBase);
285 
286  fprintf(stderr, "Param=%s\nOut=%s\nDens=%s\n", ParamFile, OutFile, DensityFile);
287  if (Perr) ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Syntax:\n%s /P:ParamFile /O:OutputFile [/AP:AirTravelFile] [/s:SchoolFile] [/D:DensityFile] [/L:NetworkFileToLoad | /S:NetworkFileToSave] [/R:R0scaling] SetupSeed1 SetupSeed2 RunSeed1 RunSeed2\n", argv[0]);
288 
292 
293 #ifdef _OPENMP
294  P.NumThreads = omp_get_max_threads();
295  if ((P.MaxNumThreads > 0) && (P.MaxNumThreads < P.NumThreads)) P.NumThreads = P.MaxNumThreads;
296  if (P.NumThreads > MAX_NUM_THREADS)
297  {
298  fprintf(stderr, "Assigned number of threads (%d) > MAX_NUM_THREADS (%d)\n", P.NumThreads, MAX_NUM_THREADS);
299  P.NumThreads = MAX_NUM_THREADS;
300  }
301  fprintf(stderr, "Using %d threads\n", P.NumThreads);
302  omp_set_num_threads(P.NumThreads);
303 
304 #pragma omp parallel default(shared)
305  {
306  fprintf(stderr, "Thread %i initialised\n", omp_get_thread_num());
307  }
308  /* fprintf(stderr,"int=%i\tfloat=%i\tdouble=%i\tint *=%i\n",(int) sizeof(int),(int) sizeof(float),(int) sizeof(double),(int) sizeof(int *)); */
309 #else
310  P.NumThreads = 1;
311 #endif
312  if (!GotPP)
313  {
314  sprintf(PreParamFile, ".." DIRECTORY_SEPARATOR "Pre_%s", ParamFile);
315  }
316 
320 
321 
322  ReadParams(ParamFile, PreParamFile);
323  if (GotScF) P.DoSchoolFile = 1;
324  if (P.DoAirports)
325  {
326  if (!GotAP) ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Syntax:\n%s /P:ParamFile /O:OutputFile /AP:AirTravelFile [/s:SchoolFile] [/D:DensityFile] [/L:NetworkFileToLoad | /S:NetworkFileToSave] [/R:R0scaling] SetupSeed1 SetupSeed2 RunSeed1 RunSeed2\n", argv[0]);
327  ReadAirTravel(AirTravelFile);
328  }
329 
333 
335  SetupModel(DensityFile, NetworkFile, SchoolFile, RegDemogFile);
336 
337  for (i = 0; i < MAX_ADUNITS; i++) AdUnits[i].NI = 0;
338  if (P.DoInterventionFile > 0)
339  for (i = 0; i < P.DoInterventionFile; i++)
340  ReadInterventions(InterventionFile[i]);
341 
342  fprintf(stderr, "Model setup in %lf seconds\n", ((double)(clock() - cl)) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
343 
344  //print out number of calls to random number generator
345 
349 
350 
351  P.NRactE = P.NRactNE = 0;
352  for (i = 0; (i < P.NR) && (P.NRactNE < P.NRN) && (!InterruptRun); i++)
353  {
354  if (P.NR > 1)
355  {
356  sprintf(OutFile, "%s.%i", OutFileBase, i);
357  fprintf(stderr, "Realisation %i (time=%lf nr_ne=%i)\n", i + 1, ((double)(clock() - cl)) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC, P.NRactNE);
358  }
359 
361  if (i == 0 || (P.ResetSeeds && P.KeepSameSeeds))
362  {
363  P.nextRunSeed1 = P.runSeed1;
364  P.nextRunSeed2 = P.runSeed2;
365  }
366  if (P.ResetSeeds) {
367  //save these seeds to file
368  SaveRandomSeeds();
369  }
370  // Now that we have set P.nextRunSeed* ready for the run, we need to save the values in case
371  // we need to reinitialise the RNG after the run is interrupted.
372  long thisRunSeed1 = P.nextRunSeed1;
373  long thisRunSeed2 = P.nextRunSeed2;
374  if (i == 0 || P.ResetSeeds) {
375  setall(&P.nextRunSeed1, &P.nextRunSeed2);
376  //fprintf(stderr, "%i, %i\n", P.newseed1,P.newseed2);
377  //fprintf(stderr, "%f\n", ranf());
378  }
379 
381  InitModel(i); //passing run number into RunModel so we can save run number in the infection event log: ggilani - 15/10/2014
382  if (P.DoLoadSnapshot) LoadSnapshot();
383  while (RunModel(i))
384  { // has been interrupted to reset holiday time. Note that this currently only happens in the first run, regardless of how many realisations are being run.
385  long tmp1 = thisRunSeed1;
386  long tmp2 = thisRunSeed2;
387  setall(&tmp1, &tmp2); // reset random number seeds to generate same run again after calibration.
388  InitModel(i);
389  }
390  if (P.OutputNonSummaryResults)
391  {
392  if (((!TimeSeries[P.NumSamples - 1].extinct) || (!P.OutputOnlyNonExtinct)) && (P.OutputEveryRealisation))
393  {
394  SaveResults();
395  }
396  }
397  if ((P.DoRecordInfEvents) && (P.RecordInfEventsPerRun == 1))
398  {
399  SaveEvents();
400  }
401  }
402  sprintf(OutFile, "%s", OutFileBase);
403 
404  //Calculate origin destination matrix if needed
405  if ((P.DoAdUnits) && (P.DoOriginDestinationMatrix))
406  {
407  CalcOriginDestMatrix_adunit();
408  SaveOriginDestMatrix();
409  }
410 
411  P.NRactual = P.NRactNE;
412  TSMean = TSMeanNE; TSVar = TSVarNE;
413  if ((P.DoRecordInfEvents) && (P.RecordInfEventsPerRun == 0))
414  {
415  SaveEvents();
416  }
417  sprintf(OutFile, "%s.avNE", OutFileBase);
418  SaveSummaryResults();
419  P.NRactual = P.NRactE;
420  TSMean = TSMeanE; TSVar = TSVarE;
421  sprintf(OutFile, "%s.avE", OutFileBase);
422  //SaveSummaryResults();
423 
424 
425 #ifdef WIN32_BM
426  Gdiplus::GdiplusShutdown(m_gdiplusToken);
427 #endif
428  fprintf(stderr, "Extinction in %i out of %i runs\n", P.NRactE, P.NRactNE + P.NRactE);
429  fprintf(stderr, "Model ran in %lf seconds\n", ((double)(clock() - cl)) / CLOCKS_PER_SEC);
430  fprintf(stderr, "Model finished\n");
431 }

434 void ReadParams(char* ParamFile, char* PreParamFile)
435 {
436  FILE* ParamFile_dat, * PreParamFile_dat, *AdminFile_dat;
437  double s, t, AgeSuscScale;
438  int i, j, k, f, nc, na;
439  char CountryNameBuf[128 * MAX_COUNTRIES], AdunitListNamesBuf[128 * MAX_ADUNITS];
440 
441  char* CountryNames[MAX_COUNTRIES];
442  for (i = 0; i < MAX_COUNTRIES; i++) { CountryNames[i] = CountryNameBuf + 128 * i; CountryNames[i][0] = 0; }
443  char* AdunitListNames[MAX_ADUNITS];
444  for (i = 0; i < MAX_ADUNITS; i++) { AdunitListNames[i] = AdunitListNamesBuf + 128 * i; AdunitListNames[i][0] = 0; }
445  if (!(ParamFile_dat = fopen(ParamFile, "rb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open parameter file\n");
446  PreParamFile_dat = fopen(PreParamFile, "rb");
447  if (!(AdminFile_dat = fopen(AdunitFile, "rb"))) AdminFile_dat = ParamFile_dat;
448  AgeSuscScale = 1.0;
449  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Update timestep", "%lf", (void*) & (P.TimeStep), 1, 1, 0);
450  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Sampling timestep", "%lf", (void*) & (P.SampleStep), 1, 1, 0);
451  if (P.TimeStep > P.SampleStep) ERR_CRITICAL("Update step must be smaller than sampling step\n");
452  t = ceil(P.SampleStep / P.TimeStep - 1e-6);
453  P.UpdatesPerSample = (int)t;
454  P.TimeStep = P.SampleStep / t;
455  P.TimeStepsPerDay = ceil(1.0 / P.TimeStep - 1e-6);
456  fprintf(stderr, "Update step = %lf\nSampling step = %lf\nUpdates per sample=%i\nTimeStepsPerDay=%lf\n", P.TimeStep, P.SampleStep, P.UpdatesPerSample, P.TimeStepsPerDay);
457  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Sampling time", "%lf", (void*) & (P.SampleTime), 1, 1, 0);
458  P.NumSamples = 1 + (int)ceil(P.SampleTime / P.SampleStep);
459  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Population size", "%i", (void*) & (P.N), 1, 1, 0);
460  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Number of realisations", "%i", (void*) & (P.NR), 1, 1, 0);
461  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Number of non-extinct realisations", "%i", (void*) & (P.NRN), 1, 1, 0)) P.NRN = P.NR;
462  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Maximum number of cases defining small outbreak", "%i", (void*) & (P.SmallEpidemicCases), 1, 1, 0)) P.SmallEpidemicCases = -1;
463  P.NC = -1;
464  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Number of micro-cells per spatial cell width", "%i", (void*) & (P.NMCL), 1, 1, 0);
465  //added parameter to reset seeds after every run
466  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Reset seeds for every run", "%i", (void*) & (P.ResetSeeds), 1, 1, 0)) P.ResetSeeds = 0;
467  if (P.ResetSeeds)
468  {
469  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Keep same seeds for every run", "%i", (void*) & (P.KeepSameSeeds), 1, 1, 0)) P.KeepSameSeeds = 0; //added this to control which seeds are used: ggilani 27/11/19
470  }
471  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Reset seeds after intervention", "%i", (void*) & (P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention), 1, 1, 0)) P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention = 0;
472  if (P.ResetSeedsPostIntervention)
473  {
474  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Time to reset seeds after intervention", "%i", (void*) & (P.TimeToResetSeeds), 1, 1, 0)) P.TimeToResetSeeds = 1000000;
475  }
476  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include households", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoHouseholds), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoHouseholds = 1;
477 
478  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputAge" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputAge) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputAge = 1;
479  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputSeverityAdminUnit" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputSeverityAdminUnit) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputSeverityAdminUnit = 1;
480  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputR0" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputR0) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputR0 = 0;
481  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputControls" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputControls) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputControls = 0;
482  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputCountry" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputCountry) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputCountry = 0;
483  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputAdUnitVar" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputAdUnitVar) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputAdUnitVar = 0;
484  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputHousehold" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputHousehold) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputHousehold = 0;
485  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputInfType" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputInfType) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputInfType = 0;
486  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputNonSeverity" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputNonSeverity) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputNonSeverity = 0;
487  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "OutputNonSummaryResults" , "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputNonSummaryResults) , 1, 1, 0)) P.OutputNonSummaryResults = 0;
488 
489  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel resolution", "%i", (void*)&P.NKR, 1, 1, 0)) P.NKR = 4000000;
490  if (P.NKR < 2000000)
491  {
492  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("[Kernel resolution] needs to be at least 2000000 - not %d", P.NKR);
493  }
494  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel higher resolution factor", "%i", (void*)&P.NK_HR, 1, 1, 0)) P.NK_HR = P.NKR / 1600;
495  if (P.NK_HR < 1 || P.NK_HR >= P.NKR)
496  {
497  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("[Kernel higher resolution factor] needs to be in range [1, P.NKR = %d) - not %d", P.NKR, P.NK_HR);
498  }
499 
500  if (P.DoHouseholds)
501  {
502  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Household size distribution", "%lf", (void*)P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0], MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, 1, 0);
503  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Household attack rate", "%lf", (void*) & (P.HouseholdTrans), 1, 1, 0);
504  GetInputParameter(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Household transmission denominator power", "%lf", (void*) & (P.HouseholdTransPow), 1, 1, 0);
505  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Correct age distribution after household allocation to exactly match specified demography", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoCorrectAgeDist), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoCorrectAgeDist = 0;
506  }
507  else
508  {
509  P.HouseholdTrans = 0.0;
510  P.HouseholdTransPow = 1.0;
511  P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][0] = 1.0;
512  for (i = 1; i < MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
513  P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i] = 0;
514  }
515  for (i = 1; i < MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
516  P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i] = P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i] + P.HouseholdSizeDistrib[0][i - 1];
517  for (i = 0; i < MAX_HOUSEHOLD_SIZE; i++)
518  P.HouseholdDenomLookup[i] = 1 / pow(((double)(i + 1)), P.HouseholdTransPow);
519  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include administrative units within countries", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAdUnits), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAdUnits = 1;
520  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Divisor for countries", "%i", (void*) & (P.CountryDivisor), 1, 1, 0)) P.CountryDivisor = 1;
521  if (P.DoAdUnits)
522  {
523  char** AdunitNames, * AdunitNamesBuf;
524  if (!(AdunitNames = (char**)malloc(3 * ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE * sizeof(char*)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
525  if (!(AdunitNamesBuf = (char*)malloc(3 * ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE * 360 * sizeof(char)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
526 
527  for (i = 0; i < ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE; i++)
528  {
529  P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[i] = -1;
530  AdunitNames[3 * i] = AdunitNamesBuf + 3 * i * 360;
531  AdunitNames[3 * i + 1] = AdunitNamesBuf + 3 * i * 360 + 60;
532  AdunitNames[3 * i + 2] = AdunitNamesBuf + 3 * i * 360 + 160;
533  }
534  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Divisor for level 1 administrative units", "%i", (void*)&(P.AdunitLevel1Divisor), 1, 1, 0)) P.AdunitLevel1Divisor = 1;
535  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Mask for level 1 administrative units", "%i", (void*)&(P.AdunitLevel1Mask), 1, 1, 0)) P.AdunitLevel1Mask = 1000000000;
536  na = (GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Codes and country/province names for admin units", "%s", (void*)AdunitNames, 3 * ADUNIT_LOOKUP_SIZE, 1, 0)) / 3;
537  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of countries to include", "%i", (void*)&nc, 1, 1, 0)) nc = 0;
538  if ((na > 0) && (nc>0))
539  {
540  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = (nc > 0);
541  nc = abs(nc);
542  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "List of names of countries to include", "%s", (nc > 1) ? ((void*)CountryNames) : ((void*)CountryNames[0]), nc, 1, 0);
543  P.NumAdunits = 0;
544  for (i = 0; i < na; i++)
545  for (j = 0; j < nc; j++)
546  if ((AdunitNames[3 * i + 1][0]) && (!strcmp(AdunitNames[3 * i + 1], CountryNames[j])) && (atoi(AdunitNames[3 * i]) != 0))
547  {
548  AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].id = atoi(AdunitNames[3 * i]);
549  P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[(AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].id % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor] = P.NumAdunits;
550  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * i + 1]) < 100) strcpy(AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].cnt_name, AdunitNames[3 * i + 1]);
551  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * i + 2]) < 200) strcpy(AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].ad_name, AdunitNames[3 * i + 2]);
552  // fprintf(stderr,"%i %s %s ## ",AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].id,AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].cnt_name,AdUnits[P.NumAdunits].ad_name);
553  P.NumAdunits++;
554  }
555  }
556  else
557  {
558  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of level 1 administrative units to include", "%i", (void*) & (P.NumAdunits), 1, 1, 0)) P.NumAdunits = 0;
559  if (P.NumAdunits > 0)
560  {
561  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = 1;
562  if (P.NumAdunits > MAX_ADUNITS) ERR_CRITICAL("MAX_ADUNITS too small.\n");
563  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "List of level 1 administrative units to include", "%s", (P.NumAdunits > 1) ? ((void*)AdunitListNames) : ((void*)AdunitListNames[0]), P.NumAdunits, 1, 0);
564  na = P.NumAdunits;
565  for (i = 0; i < P.NumAdunits; i++)
566  {
567  f = 0;
568  if (na > 0)
569  {
570  for (j = 0; (j < na) && (!f); j++) f = (!strcmp(AdunitNames[3 * j + 2], AdunitListNames[i]));
571  if(f) k = atoi(AdunitNames[3 * (j-1)]);
572  }
573  if ((na == 0) || (!f)) k = atoi(AdunitListNames[i]);
574  AdUnits[i].id = k;
575  P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[(k % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor] = i;
576  for (j = 0; j < na; j++)
577  if (atoi(AdunitNames[3 * j]) == k)
578  {
579  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * j + 1]) < 100) strcpy(AdUnits[i].cnt_name, AdunitNames[3 * j + 1]);
580  if (strlen(AdunitNames[3 * j + 2]) < 200) strcpy(AdUnits[i].ad_name, AdunitNames[3 * j + 2]);
581  j = na;
582  }
583  }
584  }
585  else
586  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = 0;
587  }
588  free(AdunitNames);
589  free(AdunitNamesBuf);
590 
591  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Output incidence by administrative unit", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAdunitOutput), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAdunitOutput = 0;
592  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Draw administrative unit boundaries on maps", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAdunitBoundaryOutput), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAdunitBoundaryOutput = 0;
593  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Correct administrative unit populations", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoCorrectAdunitPop), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoCorrectAdunitPop = 0;
594  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Fix population size at specified value", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoSpecifyPop), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoSpecifyPop = 0;
595  fprintf(stderr, "Using %i administrative units\n", P.NumAdunits);
596  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Divisor for administrative unit codes for boundary plotting on bitmaps", "%i", (void*) & (P.AdunitBitmapDivisor), 1, 1, 0)) P.AdunitBitmapDivisor = 1;
597  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Only output household to place distance distribution for one administrative unit", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit = 0;
598  if (P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit)
599  {
600  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Administrative unit for which household to place distance distribution to be output", "%i", (void*) & (P.OutputPlaceDistAdunit), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoOutputPlaceDistForOneAdunit = 0;
601  }
602  }
603  else
604  {
605  P.DoAdunitBoundaries = P.DoAdunitBoundaryOutput = P.DoAdunitOutput = P.DoCorrectAdunitPop = P.DoSpecifyPop = 0;
606  P.AdunitLevel1Divisor = 1; P.AdunitLevel1Mask = 1000000000;
607  P.AdunitBitmapDivisor = P.AdunitLevel1Divisor;
608  }
609 
610  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include age", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoAge), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAge = 1;
611  if (!P.DoAge)
612  {
613  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
614  P.PropAgeGroup[0][i] = 1.0 / NUM_AGE_GROUPS;
615  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
616  {
617  P.InitialImmunity[i] = 0;
618  P.AgeInfectiousness[i] = P.AgeSusceptibility[i] = 1;
619  P.RelativeSpatialContact[i] = P.RelativeTravelRate[i] = 1.0;
620  }
621  }
622  else
623  {
624 
625  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Initial immunity acts as partial immunity", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoPartialImmunity), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoPartialImmunity = 1;
626  if ((P.DoHouseholds)&&(!P.DoPartialImmunity))
627  {
628  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Initial immunity applied to all household members", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoWholeHouseholdImmunity), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoWholeHouseholdImmunity = 0;
629  }
630  else
631  P.DoWholeHouseholdImmunity = 0;
632  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Initial immunity profile by age", "%lf", (void*)P.InitialImmunity, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
633  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
634  P.InitialImmunity[i] = 0;
635  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Relative spatial contact rates by age", "%lf", (void*)P.RelativeSpatialContact, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
636  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
637  P.RelativeSpatialContact[i] = 1;
638  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Age-dependent infectiousness", "%lf", (void*)P.AgeInfectiousness, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
639  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
640  P.AgeInfectiousness[i] = 1.0;
641  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Age-dependent susceptibility", "%lf", (void*)P.AgeSusceptibility, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
642  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
643  P.AgeSusceptibility[i] = 1.0;
644  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Age distribution of population", "%lf", (void*)P.PropAgeGroup[0], NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0);
645  t = 0;
646  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
647  t += P.PropAgeGroup[0][i];
648  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
649  P.PropAgeGroup[0][i] /= t;
650  t = 0;
651  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
652  if (P.AgeSusceptibility[i] > t) t = P.AgeSusceptibility[i]; //peak susc has to be 1
653  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
654  P.AgeSusceptibility[i] /= t;
655  AgeSuscScale = t;
656  if (P.DoHouseholds) P.HouseholdTrans *= AgeSuscScale;
657  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Relative travel rates by age", "%lf", (void*)P.RelativeTravelRate, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 1, 0))
658  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
659  P.RelativeTravelRate[i] = 1;
660  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "WAIFW matrix", "%lf", (void*)P.WAIFW_Matrix, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, NUM_AGE_GROUPS, 0))
661  {
662  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
663  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
664  P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] = 1.0;
665  }
666  else
667  {
668  /* WAIFW matrix needs to be scaled to have max value of 1.
669  1st index of matrix specifies host being infected, second the infector.
670  Overall age variation in infectiousness/contact rates/susceptibility should be factored
671  out of WAIFW_matrix and put in Age dep infectiousness/susceptibility for efficiency. */
672  t = 0;
673  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
674  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
675  if (P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] > t) t = P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j];
676  if (t > 0)
677  {
678  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
679  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
680  P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] /= t;
681  }
682  else
683  {
684  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++)
685  for (j = 0; j < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; j++)
686  P.WAIFW_Matrix[i][j] = 1.0;
687  }
688  }
689  P.DoDeath = 0;
690  t = 0;
691  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++) t += P.AgeInfectiousness[i] * P.PropAgeGroup[0][i];
692  for (i = 0; i < NUM_AGE_GROUPS; i++) P.AgeInfectiousness[i] /= t;
693  }
694  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include spatial transmission", "%i", (void*) & (P.DoSpatial), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoSpatial = 1;
695  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel type", "%i", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelType), 1, 1, 0);
696  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel scale", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelScale), 1, 1, 0);
697  if (P.KernelOffsetScale != 1)
698  {
699  P.MoveKernelScale *= P.KernelOffsetScale;
700  }
701  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 3rd param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelP3), 1, 1, 0)) P.MoveKernelP3 = 0;
702  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 4th param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelP4), 1, 1, 0)) P.MoveKernelP4 = 0;
703  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel Shape", "%lf", (void*) & (P.MoveKernelShape), 1, 1, 0)) P.MoveKernelShape = 1.0;
704  if (P.KernelPowerScale != 1)
705  {
706  P.MoveKernelShape *= P.KernelPowerScale;
707  }
708  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel Type", "%i", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelType), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelType = P.MoveKernelType;
709  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel Scale", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelScale), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelScale = P.MoveKernelScale;
710  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel Shape", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelShape), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelShape = P.MoveKernelShape;
711  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel 3rd param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelP3), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelP3 = P.MoveKernelP3;
712  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Airport Kernel 4th param", "%lf", (void*) & (P.AirportKernelP4), 1, 1, 0)) P.AirportKernelP4 = P.MoveKernelP4;
713 
714  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Include places", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoPlaces), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoPlaces = 1;
715  if (P.DoPlaces)
716  {
717  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of types of places", "%i", (void*)&(P.PlaceTypeNum), 1, 1, 0)) P.PlaceTypeNum = 0;
718  if (P.PlaceTypeNum == 0) P.DoPlaces = P.DoAirports = 0;
719  }
720  else
721  P.PlaceTypeNum = P.DoAirports = 0;
722  if (P.DoPlaces)
723  {
724  if (P.PlaceTypeNum > NUM_PLACE_TYPES) ERR_CRITICAL("Too many place types\n");
725  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Minimum age for age group 1 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMin, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
726  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Maximum age for age group 1 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMax, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
727  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Proportion of age group 1 in place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
728  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Proportion of age group 2 in place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup2), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
729  {
730  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
731  {
732  P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup2[i] = 0;
733  P.PlaceTypeAgeMin2[i] = 0;
734  P.PlaceTypeAgeMax2[i] = 1000;
735  }
736  }
737  else
738  {
739  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Minimum age for age group 2 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMin2, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
740  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Maximum age for age group 2 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMax2, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
741  }
742  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Proportion of age group 3 in place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup3), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
743  {
744  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
745  {
746  P.PlaceTypePropAgeGroup3[i] = 0;
747  P.PlaceTypeAgeMin3[i] = 0;
748  P.PlaceTypeAgeMax3[i] = 1000;
749  }
750  }
751  else
752  {
753  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Minimum age for age group 3 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMin3, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
754  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Maximum age for age group 3 in place types", "%i", (void*)P.PlaceTypeAgeMax3, P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
755  }
756  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel shape params for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelShape), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
757  {
758  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
759  {
760  P.PlaceTypeKernelShape[i] = P.MoveKernelShape;
761  P.PlaceTypeKernelScale[i] = P.MoveKernelScale;
762  }
763  }
764  else
765  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel scale params for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelScale), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
766  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 3rd param for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelP3), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
767  {
768  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
769  {
770  P.PlaceTypeKernelP3[i] = P.MoveKernelP3;
771  P.PlaceTypeKernelP4[i] = P.MoveKernelP4;
772  }
773  }
774  else
775  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Kernel 4th param for place types", "%lf", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeKernelP4), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0);
776  if (!GetInputParameter2(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of closest places people pick from (0=all) for place types", "%i", (void*) & (P.PlaceTypeNearestNeighb), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
777  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
778  P.PlaceTypeNearestNeighb[i] = 0;
779  if (P.DoAdUnits)
780  {
781  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Degree to which crossing administrative unit boundaries to go to places is inhibited", "%lf", (void*) & (P.InhibitInterAdunitPlaceAssignment), P.PlaceTypeNum, 1, 0))
782  for (i = 0; i < NUM_PLACE_TYPES; i++)
783  P.InhibitInterAdunitPlaceAssignment[i] = 0;
784  }
785 
786  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Include air travel", "%i", (void*)&(P.DoAirports), 1, 1, 0)) P.DoAirports = 0;
787  if (!P.DoAirports)
788  {
789  // Airports disabled => all places are not to do with airports, and we
790  // have no hotels.
791  P.PlaceTypeNoAirNum = P.PlaceTypeNum;
792  P.HotelPlaceType = P.PlaceTypeNum;
793  }
794  else
795  {
796  // When airports are activated we must have at least one airport place
797  // // and a hotel type.
798  GetInputParameter(PreParamFile_dat, AdminFile_dat, "Number of non-airport places", "%i", (void*)&(P.PlaceTypeNoAirNum), 1, 1, 0);

950  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Infectiousness profile", "%lf", (void*)P.infectious_prof, INFPROF_RES, 1, 0))
951  {
952  for (i = 0; i < INFPROF_RES; i++)
953  P.infectious_prof[i] = 1;
954  }
955  k = (int)ceil(P.InfectiousPeriod / P.TimeStep);
956  if (k >= MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS) ERR_CRITICAL("MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS not big enough\n");
957  s = 0;
958  P.infectious_prof[INFPROF_RES] = 0;
959  for (i = 0; i < MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS; i++) P.infectiousness[i] = 0;
960  for (i = 0; i < k; i++)
961  {
962  t = (((double)i) * P.TimeStep / P.InfectiousPeriod * INFPROF_RES);
963  j = (int)t;
964  t -= (double)j;
965  if (j < INFPROF_RES)
966  s += (P.infectiousness[i] = P.infectious_prof[j] * (1 - t) + P.infectious_prof[j + 1] * t);
967  else
968  s += (P.infectiousness[i] = P.infectious_prof[INFPROF_RES]);
969  }
970  s /= ((double)k);
971  for (i = 0; i <= k; i++) P.infectiousness[i] /= s;
972  for (i = 0; i <= CDF_RES; i++) P.infectious_icdf[i] = exp(-1.0);
973  }
974  else
975  {
976  if (!GetInputParameter2(ParamFile_dat, PreParamFile_dat, "Infectious period inverse CDF", "%lf", (void*)P.infectious_icdf, CDF_RES + 1, 1, 0))
977  {
978  P.infectious_icdf[CDF_RES] = 100;
979  for (i = 0; i < CDF_RES; i++)
980  P.infectious_icdf[i] = -log(1 - ((double)i) / CDF_RES);
981  }
982  k = (int)ceil(P.InfectiousPeriod * P.infectious_icdf[CDF_RES] / P.TimeStep);
983  if (k >= MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS) ERR_CRITICAL("MAX_INFECTIOUS_STEPS not big enough\n");
984  for (i = 0; i < k; i++) P.infectiousness[i] = 1.0;
985  P.infectiousness[k] = 0;
986  for (i = 0; i <= CDF_RES; i++) P.infectious_icdf[i] = exp(-P.infectious_icdf[i]);
987  }

2027  for (t = 0; t <= 360; t++)
2028  {

2035 void ReadInterventions(char* IntFile)
2036 {
2037  FILE* dat;
2038  double r, s, startt, stopt;
2039  int j, k, au, ni, f, nsr;
2040  char buf[65536], txt[65536];
2041  intervention CurInterv;
2042 
2043  fprintf(stderr, "Reading intervention file.\n");
2044  if (!(dat = fopen(IntFile, "rb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open intervention file\n");
2045  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]") != 0) { // needs to be separate line because start of file
2046  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2047  }
2048  if(fscanf(dat, "<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {
2049  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2050  }
2051  if (strcmp(txt, "\?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"ISO-8859-1\"\?") != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Intervention file not XML.\n");
2052  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {
2053  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2054  }
2055  if (strcmp(txt, "InterventionSettings") != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Intervention has no top level.\n");
2056  ni = 0;
2057  while (!feof(dat))
2058  {
2059  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {
2060  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2061  }
2062  if (strcmp(txt, "intervention") == 0)
2063  {
2064  ni++;
2065  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {
2066  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2067  }
2068  if (strcmp(txt, "parameters") != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2069  if (!GetXMLNode(dat, "Type", "parameters", txt, 1)) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2070  if (strcmp(txt, "Treatment") == 0)
2071  CurInterv.InterventionType = 0;
2072  else if (strcmp(txt, "Vaccination") == 0)
2073  CurInterv.InterventionType = 1;
2074  else if (strcmp(txt, "ITN") == 0)
2075  CurInterv.InterventionType = 2;
2076  else if (strcmp(txt, "IRS") == 0)
2077  CurInterv.InterventionType = 3;
2078  else if (strcmp(txt, "GM") == 0)
2079  CurInterv.InterventionType = 4;
2080  else if (strcmp(txt, "MSAT") == 0)
2081  CurInterv.InterventionType = 5;
2082  else
2083  sscanf(txt, "%i", &CurInterv.InterventionType);
2084  if (!GetXMLNode(dat, "AUThresh", "parameters", txt, 1)) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2085  sscanf(txt, "%i", &CurInterv.DoAUThresh);
2086  if (!GetXMLNode(dat, "StartTime", "parameters", txt, 1)) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2087  sscanf(txt, "%lf", &CurInterv.StartTime);
2088  startt = CurInterv.StartTime;
2089  if (!GetXMLNode(dat, "StopTime", "parameters", txt, 1)) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2090  sscanf(txt, "%lf", &CurInterv.StopTime);
2091  stopt = CurInterv.StopTime;
2092  if (!GetXMLNode(dat, "MinDuration", "parameters", txt, 1)) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");

2119  sscanf(txt, "%lf", &CurInterv.LevelCountryVar);
2120  else

2124  else

2127  sscanf(txt, "%lf", &CurInterv.ControlParam);
2128  else
2129  CurInterv.ControlParam = 0;

2131  sscanf(txt, "%lf", &CurInterv.TimeOffset);
2132  else
2133  CurInterv.TimeOffset = 0;
2134 
2135  if (!GetXMLNode(dat, "MaxRounds", "parameters", txt, 1)) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2136  sscanf(txt, "%u", &CurInterv.MaxRounds);

2138  sscanf(txt, "%u", &CurInterv.MaxResource);

2140  sscanf(txt, "%i", &nsr);
2141  else
2142  nsr = 0;
2143  do {
2144  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {

2146  }
2147  } while ((strcmp(txt, "/intervention") != 0) && (strcmp(txt, "/parameters") != 0) && (!feof(dat)));
2148  if (strcmp(txt, "/parameters") != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete intervention parameter specification in intervention file\n");
2149  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {
2150  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2151  }

2153  if (strcmp(txt, "adunits") == 0)
2154  {
2155  while (GetXMLNode(dat, "A", "adunits", buf, 0))
2156  {
2157  sscanf(buf, "%s", txt);
2158  j = atoi(txt);
2159  if (j == 0)
2160  {
2161  f = 1; au = -1;
2162  do
2163  {
2164  au++; f = strcmp(txt, AdUnits[au].ad_name);
2165  } while ((f) && (au < P.NumAdunits));
2166  if (!f)
2167  {
2168  r = fabs(CurInterv.Level) + (2.0 * ranf() - 1) * CurInterv.LevelAUVar;
2169  if ((CurInterv.Level < 1) && (r > 1))
2170  r = 1;
2171  else if (r < 0)
2172  r = 0;
2173  for (k = 0; k <= nsr; k++)
2174  {

2176  AdUnits[au].InterventionList[AdUnits[au].NI].Level = r;
2177  AdUnits[au].InterventionList[AdUnits[au].NI].StartTime = startt + ((double)k) * (stopt - startt);
2178  AdUnits[au].InterventionList[AdUnits[au].NI].StopTime = stopt + ((double)k) * (stopt - startt);
2179  AdUnits[au].NI++;
2180  }
2181  }
2182  }
2183  else
2184  {
2185  k = (j % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor;
2186  au = P.AdunitLevel1Lookup[k];
2187  if ((au >= 0) && (AdUnits[au].id / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor == j / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor))
2188  {
2189  r = CurInterv.Level + (2.0 * ranf() - 1) * CurInterv.LevelAUVar;
2190  if ((CurInterv.Level < 1) && (r > 1))
2191  r = 1;
2192  else if (r < 0)
2193  r = 0;
2194  for (k = 0; k <= nsr; k++)
2195  {
2196  AdUnits[au].InterventionList[AdUnits[au].NI] = CurInterv;

2200  AdUnits[au].NI++;
2201  }
2202  }
2203  }
2204  }
2205  }
2206  else
2207  {

2209  {

2214  if (((j == 0) && (strcmp(txt, AdUnits[au].cnt_name) == 0)) || ((j > 0) && (j == AdUnits[au].cnt_id)))
2215  {

2217  if ((CurInterv.Level < 1) && (r > 1))
2218  r = 1;
2219  else if (r < 0)
2220  r = 0;

2222  {

2224  AdUnits[au].InterventionList[AdUnits[au].NI].Level = r;

2226  AdUnits[au].InterventionList[AdUnits[au].NI].StopTime = stopt + ((double)k) * (stopt - startt);
2227  AdUnits[au].NI++;
2228  }
2229  }

2231  }
2232  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", txt) != 1) {
2233  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in ReadInterventions\n");
2234  }
2235  if (strcmp(txt, "/intervention") != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incorrect intervention specification in intervention file\n");
2236  }
2237  }
2238  if (strcmp(txt, "/InterventionSettings") != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Intervention has no top level closure.\n");
2239  fprintf(stderr, "%i interventions read\n", ni);
2240  fclose(dat);
2241 }
2242 int GetXMLNode(FILE* dat, const char* NodeName, const char* ParentName, char* Value, int ResetFilePos)
2243 {
2244  // ResetFilePos=1 leaves dat cursor in same position as when function was called. 0 leaves it at end of NodeName closure
2245  // GetXMLNode returns 1 if NodeName found, 0 otherwise. If NodeName not found, ParentName closure must be
2246 
2247  char buf[65536], CloseNode[2048], CloseParent[2048];
2248  int CurPos, ret;
2249 
2250  sprintf(CloseParent, "/%s", ParentName);
2251  CurPos = ftell(dat);
2252  do
2253  {
2254  if(fscanf(dat, "%*[^<]<%[^>]", buf) != 1) {
2255  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in GetXMLNode");
2256  }
2257  } while ((strcmp(buf, CloseParent) != 0) && (strcmp(buf, NodeName) != 0) && (!feof(dat)));
2258  if (strcmp(buf, CloseParent) == 0)
2259  ret = 0;
2260  else
2261  {
2262  if (strcmp(buf, NodeName) != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete node specification in XML file\n");
2263  if(fscanf(dat, ">%[^<]", buf) != 1) {
2264  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in GetXMLNode");
2265  }
2266  if (strlen(buf) < 2048) strcpy(Value, buf);
2267  // fprintf(stderr,"# %s=%s\n",NodeName,Value);
2268  if(fscanf(dat, "<%[^>]", buf) != 1) {
2269  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in GetXMLNode");
2270  }
2271  sprintf(CloseNode, "/%s", NodeName);
2272  if (strcmp(buf, CloseNode) != 0) ERR_CRITICAL("Incomplete node specification in XML file\n");
2273  ret = 1;
2274  }
2275  if (ResetFilePos) fseek(dat, CurPos, 0);
2276  return ret;
2277 }
2278 void ReadAirTravel(char* AirTravelFile)
2279 {
2280  int i, j, k, l;
2281  float sc, t, t2;
2282  float* buf;
2283  double traf;
2284  char outname[1024];
2285  FILE* dat;
2286 
2287  fprintf(stderr, "Reading airport data...\nAirports with no connections = ");
2288  if (!(dat = fopen(AirTravelFile, "rb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open airport file\n");
2289  if(fscanf(dat, "%i %i", &P.Nairports, &P.Air_popscale) != 2) {
2290  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in void ReadAirTravel\n");
2291  }
2292  sc = (float)((double)P.N / (double)P.Air_popscale);
2293  if (P.Nairports > MAX_AIRPORTS) ERR_CRITICAL("Too many airports\n");
2294  if (P.Nairports < 2) ERR_CRITICAL("Too few airports\n");
2295  if (!(buf = (float*)calloc(P.Nairports + 1, sizeof(float)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2296  if (!(Airports = (airport*)calloc(P.Nairports, sizeof(airport)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2297  for (i = 0; i < P.Nairports; i++)
2298  {
2299  if(fscanf(dat, "%f %f %lf", &(Airports[i].loc_x), &(Airports[i].loc_y), &traf) != 3) {
2300  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in void ReadAirTravel\n");
2301  }
2302  traf *= (P.AirportTrafficScale * sc);
2303  if ((Airports[i].loc_x < P.SpatialBoundingBox[0]) || (Airports[i].loc_x > P.SpatialBoundingBox[2])
2304  || (Airports[i].loc_y < P.SpatialBoundingBox[1]) || (Airports[i].loc_y > P.SpatialBoundingBox[3]))
2305  {
2306  Airports[i].loc_x = Airports[i].loc_y = -1;
2307  Airports[i].total_traffic = 0;
2308  }
2309  else
2310  {
2311  //fprintf(stderr,"(%f\t%f) ",Airports[i].loc_x,Airports[i].loc_y);
2312  Airports[i].loc_x -= (float)P.SpatialBoundingBox[0];
2313  Airports[i].loc_y -= (float)P.SpatialBoundingBox[1];
2314  Airports[i].total_traffic = (float)traf;
2315  }
2316  t = 0;
2317  for (j = k = 0; j < P.Nairports; j++)
2318  {
2319  if(fscanf(dat, "%f", buf + j) != 1) {
2320  ERR_CRITICAL("fscanf failed in void ReadAirTravel\n");
2321  }
2322  if (buf[j] > 0) { k++; t += buf[j]; }
2323  }
2324  Airports[i].num_connected = k;
2325  if (Airports[i].num_connected > 0)
2326  {
2327  if (!(Airports[i].prop_traffic = (float*)calloc(Airports[i].num_connected, sizeof(float)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2328  if (!(Airports[i].conn_airports = (unsigned short int*) calloc(Airports[i].num_connected, sizeof(unsigned short int)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate airport storage\n");
2329  for (j = k = 0; j < P.Nairports; j++)
2330  if (buf[j] > 0)
2331  {
2332  Airports[i].conn_airports[k] = j;
2333  Airports[i].prop_traffic[k] = buf[j] / t;
2334  k++;
2335  }
2336  }
2337  else
2338  {
2339  if (Airports[i].total_traffic > 0)
2340  fprintf(stderr, "#%i# ", i);
2341  else
2342  fprintf(stderr, "%i ", i);
2343  }
2344  }
2345  fclose(dat);
2346  free(buf);
2347  fprintf(stderr, "\nAirport data read OK.\n");
2348  for (i = 0; i < P.Nairports; i++)
2349  {
2350  /* fprintf(stderr,"(%f %i|",Airports[i].total_traffic,Airports[i].num_connected);
2351  */ t = 0; k = 0;
2352  for (j = Airports[i].num_connected - 1; j >= 0; j--)
2353  {
2354  if ((Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] > 0) && (Airports[Airports[i].conn_airports[j]].total_traffic == 0))
2355  {
2356  t += Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2357  Airports[i].num_connected--;
2358  if (j < Airports[i].num_connected)
2359  {
2360  Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] = Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected];
2361  Airports[i].conn_airports[j] = Airports[i].conn_airports[Airports[i].num_connected];
2362  }
2363  Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected] = 0;
2364  Airports[i].conn_airports[Airports[i].num_connected] = 0;
2365  }
2366  else if (Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] > 0)
2367  k = 1;
2368  }
2369  /* fprintf(stderr,"%f %i ",t,k);
2370  */ t = 1.0f - t;
2371  if (k)
2372  {
2373  Airports[i].total_traffic *= t;
2374  t2 = 0;
2375  for (j = 0; j < Airports[i].num_connected; j++)
2376  {
2377  Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] = t2 + Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2378  t2 = Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2379  }
2380  for (j = 0; j < Airports[i].num_connected; j++)
2381  Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] /= t2;
2382  /* if((Airports[i].num_connected>0)&&(Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected-1]!=1))
2383  fprintf(stderr,"<%f> ",Airports[i].prop_traffic[Airports[i].num_connected-1]);
2384  */
2385  }
2386  else
2387  {
2388  Airports[i].total_traffic = 0; Airports[i].num_connected = 0;
2389  }
2390  if (Airports[i].num_connected > 0)
2391  {
2392  for (j = k = 0; k < 128; k++)
2393  {
2394  t = (float)((double)k / 128);
2395  while (Airports[i].prop_traffic[j] < t) j++;
2396  Airports[i].Inv_prop_traffic[k] = j;
2397  }
2398  Airports[i].Inv_prop_traffic[128] = Airports[i].num_connected - 1;
2399  }
2400  /* fprintf(stderr,"%f) ",Airports[i].total_traffic);
2401  */
2402  }
2403  fprintf(stderr, "Airport data clipped OK.\n");
2404  for (i = 0; i < MAX_DIST; i++) AirTravelDist[i] = 0;
2405  for (i = 0; i < P.Nairports; i++)
2406  if (Airports[i].total_traffic > 0)
2407  {
2408  for (j = 0; j < Airports[i].num_connected; j++)
2409  {
2410  k = (int)Airports[i].conn_airports[j];
2411  traf = floor(sqrt(dist2_raw(Airports[i].loc_x, Airports[i].loc_y, Airports[k].loc_x, Airports[k].loc_y)) / OUTPUT_DIST_SCALE);
2412  l = (int)traf;
2413  //fprintf(stderr,"%(%i) ",l);
2414  if (l < MAX_DIST)
2415  AirTravelDist[l] += Airports[i].total_traffic * Airports[i].prop_traffic[j];
2416  }
2417  }
2418  sprintf(outname, "%s.airdist.xls", OutFile);
2419  if (!(dat = fopen(outname, "wb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open air travel output file\n");
2420  fprintf(dat, "dist\tfreq\n");
2421  for (i = 0; i < MAX_DIST; i++)
2422  fprintf(dat, "%i\t%.10f\n", i, AirTravelDist[i]);
2423  fclose(dat);
2424 }

2753 void SeedInfection(double t, int* nsi, int rf, int run) //adding run number to pass it to event log
2754 {
2755  /* *nsi is an array of the number of seeding infections by location (I think). During runtime, usually just a single int (given by a poisson distribution)*/
2756  /*rf set to 0 when initializing model, otherwise set to 1 during runtime. */
2757 
2758  int i /*seed location index*/;
2759  int j /*microcell number*/;
2760  int k, l /*k,l are grid coords at first, then l changed to be person within Microcell j, then k changed to be index of new infection*/;
2761  int m = 0/*guard against too many infections and infinite loop*/;
2762  int f /*range = {0, 1000}*/;
2763  int n /*number of seed locations?*/;
2764 
2765  n = ((rf == 0) ? P.NumSeedLocations : 1);
2766  for (i = 0; i < n; i++)
2767  {
2768  if ((!P.DoRandomInitialInfectionLoc) || ((P.DoAllInitialInfectioninSameLoc) && (rf)))
2769  {
2770  k = (int)(P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] / P.mcwidth);
2771  l = (int)(P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] / P.mcheight);
2772  j = k * P.nmch + l;
2773  m = 0;
2774  for (k = 0; (k < nsi[i]) && (m < 10000); k++)
2775  {
2776  l = Mcells[j].members[(int)(ranf() * ((double)Mcells[j].n))];
2777  if (Hosts[l].inf == InfStat_Susceptible)
2778  {
2779  if (CalcPersonSusc(l, 0, 0, 0) > 0)
2780  {
2781  //only reset the initial location if rf==0, i.e. when initial seeds are being set, not when imported cases are being set
2782  if (rf == 0)
2783  {
2784  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_x;
2785  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_y;
2786  }
2787  Hosts[l].infector = -2;
2788  Hosts[l].infect_type = INFECT_TYPE_MASK - 1;
2789  DoInfect(l, t, 0, run);
2790  m = 0;
2791  }
2792  }
2793  else { k--; m++; }
2794  }
2795  }
2796  else if (P.DoAllInitialInfectioninSameLoc)
2797  {
2798  f = 0;
2799  do
2800  {
2801  m = 0;
2802  do
2803  {
2804  l = (int)(ranf() * ((double)P.N));
2805  j = Hosts[l].mcell;
2806  //fprintf(stderr,"%i ",AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id);
2807  } while ((Mcells[j].n < nsi[i]) || (Mcells[j].n > P.MaxPopDensForInitialInfection)
2808  || (Mcells[j].n < P.MinPopDensForInitialInfection)
2809  || ((P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] > 0) && ((AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor != (P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor)));
2810  for (k = 0; (k < nsi[i]) && (m < 10000); k++)
2811  {
2812  l = Mcells[j].members[(int)(ranf() * ((double)Mcells[j].n))];
2813  if (Hosts[l].inf == InfStat_Susceptible)
2814  {
2815  if (CalcPersonSusc(l, 0, 0, 0) > 0)
2816  {
2817  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_x;
2818  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_y;
2819  Hosts[l].infector = -2; Hosts[l].infect_type = INFECT_TYPE_MASK - 1;
2820  DoInfect(l, t, 0, run);
2821  m = 0;
2822  }
2823  }
2824  else
2825  {
2826  k--; m++;
2827  }
2828  }
2829  if (m)
2830  f++;
2831  else
2832  f = 0;
2833  } while ((f > 0) && (f < 1000));
2834  }
2835  else
2836  {
2837  m = 0;
2838  for (k = 0; (k < nsi[i]) && (m < 10000); k++)
2839  {
2840  do
2841  {
2842  l = (int)(ranf() * ((double)P.N));
2843  j = Hosts[l].mcell;
2844  //fprintf(stderr,"@@ %i %i ",AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id, (int)(AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id / P.CountryDivisor));
2845  } while ((Mcells[j].n == 0) || (Mcells[j].n > P.MaxPopDensForInitialInfection)
2846  || (Mcells[j].n < P.MinPopDensForInitialInfection)
2847  || ((P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] > 0) && ((AdUnits[Mcells[j].adunit].id % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor != (P.InitialInfectionsAdminUnit[i] % P.AdunitLevel1Mask) / P.AdunitLevel1Divisor)));
2848  l = Mcells[j].members[(int)(ranf() * ((double)Mcells[j].n))];
2849  if (Hosts[l].inf == InfStat_Susceptible)
2850  {
2851  if (CalcPersonSusc(l, 0, 0, 0) > 0)
2852  {
2853  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][0] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_x;
2854  P.LocationInitialInfection[i][1] = Households[Hosts[l].hh].loc_y;
2855  Hosts[l].infector = -2; Hosts[l].infect_type = INFECT_TYPE_MASK - 1;
2856  DoInfect(l, t, 0, run);
2857  m = 0;
2858  }
2859  else
2860  {
2861  k--; m++;
2862  }
2863  }
2864  else
2865  {
2866  k--; m++;
2867  }
2868  }
2869  }
2870  }
2871  if (m > 0) fprintf(stderr, "### Seeding error ###\n");
2872 }

2875 int RunModel(int run) //added run number as parameter
2876 {
2877  int j, k, l, fs, fs2, nu, ni, nsi[MAX_NUM_SEED_LOCATIONS] /*Denotes either Num imported Infections given rate ir, or number false positive "infections"*/;

2890  if ((Hosts[i].pcell < P.NC) && (Hosts[i].pcell >= 0))
2891  {
2892  if (Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].susceptible[Hosts[i].listpos] != i)
2893  {
2894  k++;
2895  for (l = fs = 0; (l < Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].n) && (!fs); l++)
2896  fs = (Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].susceptible[l] == i);
2897  if (!fs) ni++;
2898  }
2899  else
2900  {

2902  if ((Hosts[i].listpos < Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].S + Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].L + Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].I - 1) && (abs(Hosts[i].inf) == InfStat_Recovered)) i2++;
2903  }
2904  if ((Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].S + Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].L + Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].I + Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].R + Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].D) != Cells[Hosts[i].pcell].n)
2905  {

2907  }
2908  }
2909  else
2910  fs2++;
2911  }
2912  fprintf(stderr, "\n*** susceptibles=%i\nincorrect listpos=%i\nhosts not found in cell list=%i\nincorrect cell refs=%i\nincorrect positioning in cell susc list=%i\nwrong cell totals=%i\n", j, k, ni, fs2, i2, k2);
2913 */
2914  InterruptRun = 0;

2916  if (P.DoLoadSnapshot)
2917  {
2918  P.ts_age = (int)(P.SnapshotLoadTime * P.TimeStepsPerDay);
2919  t = ((double)P.ts_age) * P.TimeStep;
2920  }
2921  else
2922  {
2923  t = 0;
2924  P.ts_age = 0;
2925  }

2960  else

2999  }

3676  fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumT_keyworker[j]);
3677  for(j = 0; j < 2; j++)
3678  fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSVar[i].incI_keyworker[j] - c * c * TSMean[i].incI_keyworker[j] * TSMean[i].incI_keyworker[j]);
3679  for(j = 0; j < 2; j++)
3680  fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSVar[i].incC_keyworker[j] - c * c * TSMean[i].incC_keyworker[j] * TSMean[i].incC_keyworker[j]);
3681  for(j = 0; j < 2; j++)
3682  fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSVar[i].cumT_keyworker[j] - c * c * TSMean[i].cumT_keyworker[j] * TSMean[i].cumT_keyworker[j]);

3780  double SARI, Critical, CritRecov, incSARI, incCritical, incCritRecov, sc1, sc2,sc3,sc4; //this stuff corrects bed prevalence for exponentially distributed time to test results in hospital
3781  sc1 = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-1.0 / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3782  sc2 = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3783  sc3 = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestCriticalOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3784  sc4 = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestCritRecovOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3785  incSARI = incCritical = incCritRecov = 0;
3786  for (i = 0; i < P.NumSamples; i++)
3787  {
3788  if (i > 0)
3789  {
3790  SARI = (TSMean[i].SARI - TSMean[i - 1].SARI) * sc2 + SARI * sc1;
3791  Critical = (TSMean[i].Critical - TSMean[i - 1].Critical) * sc3 + Critical * sc1;
3792  CritRecov = (TSMean[i].CritRecov - TSMean[i - 1].CritRecov) * sc4 + CritRecov * sc1;
3793  incSARI = TSMean[i].incSARI * (1.0 - sc2) + incSARI * sc1;
3794  incCritical = TSMean[i].incCritical * (1.0 - sc3) + incCritical * sc1;
3795  incCritRecov = TSMean[i].incCritRecov * (1.0 - sc4) + incCritRecov * sc1;
3796  }
3797  else
3798  {
3799  SARI = TSMean[i].SARI * sc2;
3800  Critical = TSMean[i].Critical * sc3;
3801  CritRecov = TSMean[i].CritRecov * sc4;
3802  }
3803 
3804  fprintf(dat, "%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\t%.10f\n",
3805  c* TSMean[i].t, c* TSMean[i].PropSocDist, c* TSMean[i].S, c* TSMean[i].I, c* TSMean[i].R, c* TSMean[i].incI, c* TSMean[i].incC,
3806  c* TSMean[i].Mild, c* TSMean[i].ILI, c* TSMean[i].SARI,c* TSMean[i].Critical, c* TSMean[i].CritRecov,c* (TSMean[i].SARI - SARI), c* (TSMean[i].Critical - Critical), c* (TSMean[i].CritRecov - CritRecov),
3807  c * TSMean[i].incMild, c * TSMean[i].incILI, c * TSMean[i].incSARI, c * TSMean[i].incCritical, c * TSMean[i].incCritRecov, c * incSARI, c * incCritical, c * incCritRecov, c * TSMean[i].incD,
3808  c * TSMean[i].incDeath_ILI, c * TSMean[i].incDeath_SARI, c * TSMean[i].incDeath_Critical,
3809  c * TSMean[i].cumMild, c * TSMean[i].cumILI, c * TSMean[i].cumSARI, c * TSMean[i].cumCritical, c * TSMean[i].cumCritRecov, c*TSMean[i].D,
3810  c * TSMean[i].cumDeath_ILI, c * TSMean[i].cumDeath_SARI, c * TSMean[i].cumDeath_Critical);
3811  }

3815  {
3816  double* SARI_a, * Critical_a, * CritRecov_a, * incSARI_a, * incCritical_a, * incCritRecov_a, sc1a, sc2a,sc3a,sc4a; //this stuff corrects bed prevalence for exponentially distributed time to test results in hospital
3817 
3818  if (!(SARI_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
3819  if (!(Critical_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
3820  if (!(CritRecov_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
3821  if (!(incSARI_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
3822  if (!(incCritical_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
3823  if (!(incCritRecov_a = (double*)malloc(MAX_ADUNITS * sizeof(double)))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to allocate temp storage\n");
3824  sc1a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-1.0 / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3825  sc2a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3826  sc3a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestCriticalOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3827  sc4a = (P.Mean_TimeToTest > 0) ? exp(-P.Mean_TimeToTestCritRecovOffset / P.Mean_TimeToTest) : 0.0;
3828  for (i = 0; i < P.NumAdunits; i++) incSARI_a[i] = incCritical_a[i] = incCritRecov_a[i] = 0;
3830  sprintf(outname, "%s.severity.adunit.xls", OutFile);
3831  if (!(dat = fopen(outname, "wb"))) ERR_CRITICAL("Unable to open output file\n");
3832  fprintf(dat, "t");
3833 
3836  for (i = 0; i < P.NumAdunits; i++) fprintf(dat, "\tMild_%s" , AdUnits[i].ad_name);

3844

3874  for (i = 0; i < P.NumSamples; i++)
3875  {

3877  {
3878  if (i > 0)
3879  {
3880  SARI_a[j] = (TSMean[i].SARI_adunit[j] - TSMean[i - 1].SARI_adunit[j]) * sc2a + SARI_a[j] * sc1a;
3881  Critical_a[j] = (TSMean[i].Critical_adunit[j] - TSMean[i - 1].Critical_adunit[j]) * sc3a + Critical_a[j] * sc1a;
3882  CritRecov_a[j] = (TSMean[i].CritRecov_adunit[j] - TSMean[i - 1].CritRecov_adunit[j]) * sc4a + CritRecov_a[j] * sc1a;

3884  incCritical_a[j] = TSMean[i].incCritical_adunit[j] * (1.0 - sc3a) + incCritical_a[j] * sc1a;
3885  incCritRecov_a[j] = TSMean[i].incCritRecov_adunit[j] * (1.0 - sc4a) + incCritRecov_a[j] * sc1a;

3890  Critical_a[j] = TSMean[i].Critical_adunit[j] * sc3a;
3891  CritRecov_a[j] = TSMean[i].CritRecov_adunit[j] * sc4a;
3892  }

3894  fprintf(dat, "%.10f", c*TSMean[i].t);
3896  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].Mild_adunit[j]);
3897  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].ILI_adunit[j]);
3898  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].SARI_adunit[j]);
3899  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].Critical_adunit[j]);
3900  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].CritRecov_adunit[j]);

3904 
3906  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incI_adunit[j]);
3907  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incMild_adunit[j]);
3908  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incILI_adunit[j]);
3909  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incSARI_adunit[j]);
3910  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incCritical_adunit[j]);
3911  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incCritRecov_adunit[j]);
3912  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * incSARI_a[j]);
3913  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * incCritical_a[j]);
3914  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * incCritRecov_a[j]);
3915  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incD_adunit[j]);
3916  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incDeath_ILI_adunit[j]);
3917  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incDeath_SARI_adunit[j]);
3918  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].incDeath_Critical_adunit[j]);
3919 
3921  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumMild_adunit[j]);

3923  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumSARI_adunit[j]);

3925  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumCritRecov_adunit[j]);

3927  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumDeath_ILI_adunit[j]);
3928  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumDeath_SARI_adunit[j]);
3929  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++) fprintf(dat, "\t%.10f", c * TSMean[i].cumDeath_Critical_adunit[j]);
3930 
3931  if (i != P.NumSamples - 1) fprintf(dat, "\n");
3932  }
3933  fclose(dat);
3934  free(SARI_a); free(Critical_a); free(CritRecov_a);
3935  free(incSARI_a); free(incCritical_a); free(incCritRecov_a);
3936  }
3937  }

3959 void SaveEvents(void)
3960 {
3961  /* function: SaveEvents(void)
3962  *
3963  * Purpose: outputs event log to a csv file if required
3964  * Parameters: none
3965  * Returns: none
3966  *
3967  * Author: ggilani, 15/10/2014
3968  */
3969  int i;
3970  FILE* dat;
3971  char outname[1024];

4119 void UpdateProbs(int DoPlace)
4120 {
4121  int j;
4122 
4123  if (!DoPlace)
4124  {
4125 #pragma omp parallel for private(j) schedule(static,500)
4126  for (j = 0; j < P.NCP; j++)
4127  {
4128  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob = 0;
4129  CellLookup[j]->S0 = CellLookup[j]->S + CellLookup[j]->L + CellLookup[j]->I;
4130  if (P.DoDeath)
4131  {
4132  CellLookup[j]->S0 += CellLookup[j]->n / 5;
4133  if ((CellLookup[j]->n < 100) || (CellLookup[j]->S0 > CellLookup[j]->n)) CellLookup[j]->S0 = CellLookup[j]->n;
4134  }
4135  }
4136  }
4137  else
4138  {
4139 #pragma omp parallel for private(j) schedule(static,500)
4140  for (j = 0; j < P.NCP; j++)
4141  {
4142  CellLookup[j]->S0 = CellLookup[j]->S;
4143  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob = 0;
4144  }
4145  }
4146 #pragma omp parallel for private(j) schedule(static,500)
4147  for (j = 0; j < P.NCP; j++)
4148  {
4149  int m, k;
4150  float t;
4151  CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[0] = ((float)(CellLookup[0]->S0)) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[0];
4152  t = ((float)CellLookup[0]->n) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[0];
4153  for (m = 1; m < P.NCP; m++)
4154  {
4155  CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m] = CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m - 1] + ((float)(CellLookup[m]->S0)) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[m];
4156  t += ((float)CellLookup[m]->n) * CellLookup[j]->max_trans[m];
4157  }
4158  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob = CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[P.NCP - 1];
4159  for (m = 0; m < P.NCP; m++)
4160  CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m] /= CellLookup[j]->tot_prob;
4161  CellLookup[j]->tot_prob /= t;
4162  for (k = m = 0; k <= 1024; k++)
4163  {
4164  while (CellLookup[j]->cum_trans[m] * 1024 < ((float)k)) m++;
4165  CellLookup[j]->InvCDF[k] = m;
4166  }
4167  }
4168 }

4171 int ChooseTriggerVariableAndValue(int AdUnit)
4172 {
4173  int VariableAndValue = 0;
4174  if (P.DoGlobalTriggers)
4175  {
4176  if (P.DoPerCapitaTriggers)
4177  VariableAndValue = (int)floor(((double)State.trigDC) * P.GlobalIncThreshPop / ((double)P.N));
4178  else
4179  VariableAndValue = State.trigDC;
4180  }
4181  else if (P.DoAdminTriggers) VariableAndValue = State.trigDC_adunit[AdUnit];
4182  else VariableAndValue = INT_MAX;
4183 
4184  return VariableAndValue;
4185 }
4186 double ChooseThreshold(int AdUnit, double WhichThreshold)
4187 {
4188  double Threshold = 0;
4189  if (P.DoGlobalTriggers) Threshold = WhichThreshold;
4190  else if (P.DoAdminTriggers)
4191  {
4192  if (P.DoPerCapitaTriggers)
4193  Threshold = (int)ceil(((double)(AdUnits[AdUnit].n * WhichThreshold)) / P.IncThreshPop);
4194  else
4195  Threshold = WhichThreshold;
4196  }
4197  return Threshold;
4198 }

4301 void RecordSample(double t, int n)
4302 {
4303  int i, j, k, S, L, I, R, D, N, cumC, cumTC, cumI, cumR, cumD, cumDC, cumFC;
4304  int cumH; //add number of hospitalised, cumulative hospitalisation: ggilani 28/10/14

4306  int cumCC; //added cumulative number of cases who are contacts: ggilani 28/05/2019
4307  int cumDCT; //added cumulative number of cases who are digitally contact traced: ggilani 11/03/20

4318 
4320  S = L = I = R = D = cumI = cumC = cumDC = cumTC = cumFC = cumHQ = cumAC = cumAA = cumAH = cumACS = cumAPC = cumAPA = cumAPCS = cumD = cumH = cumCT = cumCC = cumDCT = 0;

4819  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&AdUnits[i].SocialDistanceTimeStart, t + AdUnits[i].SocialDistanceDelay);
4820  }
4821  if (TriggerValue >= P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh)
4822  {
4823  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&P.PlaceCloseTimeStart, t + P.PlaceCloseTimeStartBase);
4824  if (P.DoInterventionDelaysByAdUnit)
4825  for (i = 0; i < P.NumAdunits; i++)
4826  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&AdUnits[i].PlaceCloseTimeStart, t + AdUnits[i].PlaceCloseDelay);
4827  }
4828  if (TriggerValue >= P.MoveRestrCellIncThresh)
4829  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&P.MoveRestrTimeStart, t + P.MoveRestrTimeStartBase);
4830  if (TriggerValue >= P.KeyWorkerProphCellIncThresh)
4831  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&P.KeyWorkerProphTimeStart, t + P.KeyWorkerProphTimeStartBase);
4832  }
4833  else
4834  {
4835  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&P.TreatTimeStart , t + P.TreatTimeStartBase );
4836  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&P.VaccTimeStart , t + P.VaccTimeStartBase );

4843 
4844 
4845  }
4846  if ((P.PlaceCloseIndepThresh > 0) && (((double)State.cumDC) >= P.PlaceCloseIndepThresh))
4847  DoOrDontAmendStartTime(&P.PlaceCloseTimeStart, t + P.PlaceCloseTimeStartBase);
4848

4850  if (t > P.SocDistTimeStart + P.SocDistChangeDelay)
4851  {
4852  P.SocDistDurationCurrent = P.SocDistDuration2;
4853  P.SocDistHouseholdEffectCurrent = P.SocDistHouseholdEffect2;
4854  P.SocDistSpatialEffectCurrent = P.SocDistSpatialEffect2;

4858  {
4859  P.SocDistPlaceEffectCurrent[i] = P.SocDistPlaceEffect2[i];
4860  P.EnhancedSocDistPlaceEffectCurrent[i] = P.EnhancedSocDistPlaceEffect2[i];
4861  }
4862  }
4863  //fix to switch off first place closure after P.PlaceCloseDuration has elapsed, if there are no school or cell-based triggers set
4864  if (t == P.PlaceCloseTimeStart + P.PlaceCloseDuration)
4865  {
4866  P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious = P.PlaceCloseTimeStart;
4867  if ((P.PlaceCloseIncTrig == 0) && (P.PlaceCloseFracIncTrig == 0) && (P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh == 0)) P.PlaceCloseTimeStart = 9e9;
4868  }
4869

4871  {

4873  (t >= P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious + P.PlaceCloseDuration) &&
4874  (t >= P.PlaceCloseTimeStartPrevious + P.PlaceCloseTimeStartBase2 - P.PlaceCloseTimeStartBase))
4875  {

4878  P.PlaceCloseDuration = P.PlaceCloseDuration2;
4879  P.PlaceCloseIncTrig = P.PlaceCloseIncTrig2;
4880  P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh = P.PlaceCloseCellIncThresh2;
4881  }
4882  }
4883 
4884 
4885 
4886  if (P.OutputBitmap >= 1)
4887  {
4888  TSMean = TSMeanNE; TSVar = TSVarNE;
4889  CaptureBitmap ();
4890  OutputBitmap (0);
4891  }

5047 void CalcOriginDestMatrix_adunit()
5048 {
5059  int tn, i, j, k, l, m, p;
5060  double total_flow, flow;
5061  ptrdiff_t cl_from, cl_to, cl_from_mcl, cl_to_mcl, mcl_from, mcl_to;
5062 
5063 #pragma omp parallel for private(tn,i,j,k,l,m,p,total_flow,mcl_from,mcl_to,cl_from,cl_to,cl_from_mcl,cl_to_mcl,flow) schedule(static) //reduction(+:s,t2)
5064  for (tn = 0; tn < P.NumThreads; tn++)
5065  {
5066  for (i = tn; i < P.NCP; i += P.NumThreads)
5067  {
5068  //reset pop density matrix to zero
5069  double pop_dens_from[MAX_ADUNITS] = {};
5070 
5071  //find index of cell from which flow travels
5072  cl_from = CellLookup[i] - Cells;
5073  cl_from_mcl = (cl_from / P.nch) * P.NMCL * P.nmch + (cl_from % P.nch) * P.NMCL;
5074 
5075  //loop over microcells in these cells to find populations in each admin unit and so flows
5076  for (k = 0; k < P.NMCL; k++)
5077  {
5078  for (l = 0; l < P.NMCL; l++)
5079  {
5080  //get index of microcell
5081  mcl_from = cl_from_mcl + l + k * P.nmch;
5082  if (Mcells[mcl_from].n > 0)
5083  {
5084  //get proportion of each population of cell that exists in each admin unit
5085  pop_dens_from[Mcells[mcl_from].adunit] += (((double)Mcells[mcl_from].n) / ((double)Cells[cl_from].n));
5086  }
5087  }
5088  }
5089 
5090  for (j = i; j < P.NCP; j++)
5091  {
5092  //reset pop density matrix to zero
5093  double pop_dens_to[MAX_ADUNITS] = {};
5094 
5095  //find index of cell which flow travels to
5096  cl_to = CellLookup[j] - Cells;
5097  cl_to_mcl = (cl_to / P.nch) * P.NMCL * P.nmch + (cl_to % P.nch) * P.NMCL;
5098  //calculate distance and kernel between the cells
5099  //total_flow=Cells[cl_from].max_trans[j]*Cells[cl_from].n*Cells[cl_to].n;
5100  if (j == 0)
5101  {
5102  total_flow = Cells[cl_from].cum_trans[j] * Cells[cl_from].n;
5103  }
5104  else
5105  {
5106  total_flow = (Cells[cl_from].cum_trans[j] - Cells[cl_from].cum_trans[j - 1]) * Cells[cl_from].n;
5107  }
5108 
5109  //loop over microcells within destination cell
5110  for (m = 0; m < P.NMCL; m++)
5111  {
5112  for (p = 0; p < P.NMCL; p++)
5113  {
5114  //get index of microcell
5115  mcl_to = cl_to_mcl + p + m * P.nmch;
5116  if (Mcells[mcl_to].n > 0)
5117  {
5118  //get proportion of each population of cell that exists in each admin unit
5119  pop_dens_to[Mcells[mcl_to].adunit] += (((double)Mcells[mcl_to].n) / ((double)Cells[cl_to].n));
5120  }
5121  }
5122  }
5123 
5124  for (m = 0; m < P.NumAdunits; m++)
5125  {
5126  for (p = 0; p < P.NumAdunits; p++)
5127  {
5128  if (m != p)
5129  {
5130  flow = total_flow * pop_dens_from[m] * pop_dens_to[p]; //updated to remove reference to cross-border flows: ggilani 26/03/20
5131  StateT[tn].origin_dest[m][p] += flow;
5132  StateT[tn].origin_dest[p][m] += flow;
5133  }
5134  }
5135  }
5136  }
5137 
5139  //k=(cl_from/P.nch)*P.NMCL*P.nmch+(cl_from%P.nch)*P.NMCL;
5140  //for(l=0;l<P.NMCL;l++)
5141  //{
5142  // for(m=0;m<P.NMCL;m++)
5143  // {
5144  // mcl_from=k+m+l*P.nmch;
5145  // pop_cell_from[Mcells[mcl_from].adunit]+=Mcells[mcl_from].n;
5146  // }
5147  //}
5149  //for(p=(i+1);p<P.NCP;p++)
5150  //{
5151  // //reset population array
5152  // for(j=0;j<P.NumAdunits;j++)
5153  // {
5154  // pop_cell_to[j]=0.0;
5155  // }
5156  // cl_to=CellLookup[p]-Cells;
5157  // //loop over microcells within cell to find the proportion of the cell population in each admin unit
5158  // q=(cl_to/P.nch)*P.NMCL*P.nmch+(cl_to%P.nch)*P.NMCL;
5159  // for(l=0;l<P.NMCL;l++)
5160  // {
5161  // for(m=0;m<P.NMCL;m++)
5162  // {
5163  // mcl_to=q+m+l*P.nmch;
5164  // pop_cell_to[Mcells[mcl_to].adunit]+=Mcells[mcl_to].n;
5165  // }
5166  // }
5167 
5168  // //find distance and kernel function between cells
5169  // dist=dist2_cc_min(Cells+cl_from,Cells+cl_to);
5170  // dist_kernel=numKernel(dist);
5171 
5172  // //add flow between adunits based on how population is distributed
5173  // for(l=0;l<P.NumAdunits;l++)
5174  // {
5175  // for(m=(l+1);m<P.NumAdunits;m++)
5176  // {
5177  // AdUnits[l].origin_dest[m]+=pop_cell_from[l]*pop_cell_to[m]*dist_kernel;
5178  // AdUnits[m].origin_dest[l]+=pop_cell_from[l]*pop_cell_to[m]*dist_kernel;
5179  // }
5180  // }
5181 
5182  }
5183  }
5184 
5185  //Sum up flow between adunits across threads
5186  for (i = 0; i < P.NumAdunits; i++)
5187  {
5188  for (j = 0; j < P.NumAdunits; j++)
5189  {
5190  for (k = 0; k < P.NumThreads; k++)
5191  {
5192  AdUnits[i].origin_dest[j] += StateT[k].origin_dest[i][j];
5193  }
5194  }
5195  }
5196 
5197 }

5221 /*
5222  Reads a string (as per fscanf %s).
5223  Returns true if it succeeds, false on EOF, and does not return on error.
5224 */
5225 bool readString(const char* SItemName, FILE* dat, char *buf) {
5226  int r = fscanf(dat, "%s", buf);
5227  if(r == 1) {
5228  return true;
5229  } else if (r == EOF) {
5230  if(ferror(dat)) {
5231  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("fscanf failed for %s: %s.\n", SItemName, strerror(errno));
5232  } else {
5233  // EOF
5234  return false;
5235  }
5236  } else {
5237  ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("Unexpected fscanf result %d for %s.\n", r, SItemName);
5238  }
5239 }

5241 int GetInputParameter3(FILE* dat, const char* SItemName, const char* ItemType, void* ItemPtr, int NumItem, int NumItem2, int Offset)
5242 {
5243  char match[10000] = "", ReadItemName[10000] = "", ItemName[10000];
5244  int FindFlag = 0, EndString, CurPos, i, j, n;
5245 
5246  n = 0;
5247  fseek(dat, 0, 0);
5248  sprintf(ItemName, "[%s]", SItemName);
5249  while (!FindFlag)
5250  {
5251  if(!readString(SItemName, dat, match)) return 0;
5252  FindFlag = (!strncmp(match, ItemName, strlen(match)));
5253  if (FindFlag)
5254  {
5255  CurPos = ftell(dat);
5256  strcpy(ReadItemName, match);
5257  EndString = (match[strlen(match) - 1] == ']');
5258  while ((!EndString) && (FindFlag))
5259  {
5260  if(!readString(SItemName, dat, match)) return 0;
5261  strcat(ReadItemName, " ");
5262  strcat(ReadItemName, match);
5263  FindFlag = (!strncmp(ReadItemName, ItemName, strlen(ReadItemName)));
5264  EndString = (ReadItemName[strlen(ReadItemName) - 1] == ']');
5265  }
5266  if (!EndString)
5267  {
5268  fseek(dat, CurPos, 0);
5269  FindFlag = 0;
5270  }
5271  }
5272  }
5273  if (FindFlag)
5274  {
5275  FindFlag = 0;
5276  if (!strcmp(ItemType, "%lf")) n = 1;
5277  else if (!strcmp(ItemType, "%i")) n = 2;
5278  else if (!strcmp(ItemType, "%s")) n = 3;
5279  if (NumItem2 < 2)
5280  {
5281  if (NumItem == 1)
5282  {
5283  if(fscanf(dat, "%s", match) != 1) { ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("fscanf failed for %s\n", SItemName); }
5284  if ((match[0] == '#') && (match[1] == '1'))
5285  {
5286  FindFlag++;
5287  if (n == 1)
5288  * ((double*)ItemPtr) = P.clP1;
5289  else if (n == 2)
5290  * ((int*)ItemPtr) = (int)P.clP1;
5291  else if (n == 3)
5292  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5293  }
5294  else if ((match[0] == '#') && (match[1] == '2'))
5295  {
5296  FindFlag++;
5297  if (n == 1)
5298  * ((double*)ItemPtr) = P.clP2;
5299  else if (n == 2)
5300  * ((int*)ItemPtr) = (int)P.clP2;
5301  else if (n == 3)
5302  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5303  }
5304  else if((match[0] == '#') && (match[1] == '3'))
5305  {
5306  FindFlag++;
5307  if(n == 1)
5308  * ((double*)ItemPtr) = P.clP3;
5309  else if(n == 2)
5310  * ((int*)ItemPtr) = (int)P.clP3;
5311  else if(n == 3)
5312  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5313  }
5314  else if((match[0] == '#') && (match[1] == '4'))
5315  {
5316  FindFlag++;
5317  if(n == 1)
5318  * ((double*)ItemPtr) = P.clP4;
5319  else if(n == 2)
5320  * ((int*)ItemPtr) = (int)P.clP4;
5321  else if(n == 3)
5322  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5323  }
5324  else if((match[0] == '#') && (match[1] == '5'))
5325  {
5326  FindFlag++;
5327  if(n == 1)
5328  * ((double*)ItemPtr) = P.clP5;
5329  else if(n == 2)
5330  * ((int*)ItemPtr) = (int)P.clP5;
5331  else if(n == 3)
5332  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5333  }
5334  else if((match[0] == '#') && (match[1] == '6'))
5335  {
5336  FindFlag++;
5337  if(n == 1)
5338  * ((double*)ItemPtr) = P.clP6;
5339  else if(n == 2)
5340  * ((int*)ItemPtr) = (int)P.clP6;
5341  else if(n == 3)
5342  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5343  }
5344  else if ((match[0] != '[') && (!feof(dat)))
5345  {
5346  FindFlag++;
5347  if (n == 1)
5348  sscanf(match, "%lf", (double*)ItemPtr);
5349  else if (n == 2)
5350  sscanf(match, "%i", (int*)ItemPtr);
5351  else if (n == 3)
5352  sscanf(match, "%s", (char*)ItemPtr);
5353  }
5354  }
5355  else
5356  {
5357  for (CurPos = 0; CurPos < NumItem; CurPos++)
5358  {
5359  if(fscanf(dat, "%s", match) != 1) { ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("fscanf failed for %s\n", SItemName); }
5360  if ((match[0] != '[') && (!feof(dat)))
5361  {
5362  FindFlag++;
5363  if (n == 1)
5364  sscanf(match, "%lf", ((double*)ItemPtr) + CurPos + Offset);
5365  else if (n == 2)
5366  sscanf(match, "%i", ((int*)ItemPtr) + CurPos + Offset);
5367  else if (n == 3)
5368  sscanf(match, "%s", *(((char**)ItemPtr) + CurPos + Offset));
5369  }
5370  else
5371  CurPos = NumItem;
5372  }
5373  }
5374  }
5375  else
5376  {
5377  for (j = 0; j < NumItem; j++)
5378  { //added these braces
5379  for (i = 0; i < NumItem2; i++)
5380  {
5381  if(fscanf(dat, "%s", match) != 1) { ERR_CRITICAL_FMT("fscanf failed for %s\n", SItemName); }
5382  if ((match[0] != '[') && (!feof(dat)))
5383  {
5384  FindFlag++;
5385  if (n == 1)
5386  sscanf(match, "%lf", ((double**)ItemPtr)[j + Offset] + i + Offset); //changed from [j+Offset]+i+Offset to +j+Offset+i, as ItemPtr isn't an array - 01/10: changed it back
5387  else
5388  sscanf(match, "%i", ((int**)ItemPtr)[j + Offset] + i + Offset);
5389  }
5390  else
5391  {
5392  i = NumItem2;
5393  j = NumItem;
5394  }
5395  }
5396  //Offset=Offset+(NumItem2-1); //added this line to get the correct offset in address position when incrementing j
5397  } //added these braces
5398  }
5399  }
5400  // fprintf(stderr,"%s\n",SItemName);
5401  return FindFlag;
5402 }
